      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Little Princess</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brown University philosophy Prof Felicia Ackerman letter on July 9 Lives essay notes feminists would likely object to 7-year-old Dotti-Dawn Stephens' assertion that four years of beauty pageants have changed her</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>'Dotti-Dawn knows that four years of beauty pageants have changed her, and she's glad.'' So who's to object? Lots of feminists, no doubt, who are bound to be sure they know Dotti-Dawn better than she knows herself. What chutzpah.</p>
        <p>Felicia Ackerman  Department of Philosophy  Brown University  Providence, R.I.</p>
      </block>
